-- Brazilian Stock Movers: EcoRodovias, Eletrobras and Petrobras
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2012-03-16T15:11:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/brazilian-stock-movers-ecorodovias-eletrobras-and-petrobras.html
The following companies are having
 unusual  price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:53 a.m. local time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index climbed 0.1 percent to 67,817.31.  Centrais Eletricas Brasileiras SA (ELET6)  (ELET6 BS) slid 0.6
percent to 24.15 reais. Latin America’s largest publicly traded
utility, which is controlled by the Brazilian government, was
cut to the equivalent of sell at JPMorgan Chase & Co.  EcoRodovias Infraestrutura & Logistica SA (ECOR3)  (ECOR3 BS)
climbed 0.6 percent to 15.85 reais. The Sao Paulo-based highways
and ports operator reported fourth-quarter net income of 102.8
million reais ($57.1 million), a 31 percent increase from a year
before, according to a regulatory filing.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) fell 0.5 percent to 24.10
reais.  Brazil ’s state-controlled oil company said its $224.7
billion investment plan for the 2011-2015 period is maintained
and denied speculation that it’s discussing cuts in the program,
according to an e-mailed statement yesterday. Veja magazine
reported on March 14 that Petrobras would announce a cut in the
investment plan today. The magazine didn’t say where it obtained
the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in  Sao Paulo  at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
